'''Botanomancy''' is the art of [[divination]] by burning branches of trees or herbs.<ref>{{cite news|author = Geoffrey Taylor|title = Terms Of Reference: Why Pythagoras never had a theorem on brochomancy|quote = |publisher = The Guardian |date = December 7, 1987|url =}}</ref> The most common branches used are [[Vervain]] and [[Briar (thicket)|Briar]].<ref name="book">{{Cite encyclopedia  | title = Botanomancy  | encyclopedia = The Element Encyclopedia of the Psychic World  | volume =   | pages = 84 | publisher = Harper Element  | year = 2006  | id =}}</ref> The fire and the smoke are both read to indicate which course of action should be taken.<ref name="book"/> Botanomancy can be traced back to [[Druid]]ic tree worship.<ref name="book"/>

