{{Infobox temple | name = Karya Siddhi Hanuman Temple | image = | alt = | caption = | map_type = USA Texas | map_caption = Location in Texas | coordinates = {{coord|33.178510|-96.748377|type:landmark_region:US-OH|display=inline,title}} | other_names = | proper_name = | country = United States | state = [[Texas]] | location = [[Frisco, Texas|Frisco]] | elevation_m = | deity = | primary_deity_Godess = | utsava_deity_God = | utsava_deity_Godess= | Direction_posture = | Pushakarani = | Vimanam = | Poets = | Prathyaksham = | festivals= | address = | architecture = | temple_quantity = | monument_quantity= | inscriptions = | year_completed = 2009 | creator = | website = {{URL|http://www.dallashanuman.org/}} }}
'''Karya Siddhi Hanuman Temple''' is a Hindu temple in [[Frisco, Texas]]. Its one of the biggest temple in the area. Construction on the temple started around 2007 for Hindus in the [[Dallas-Fort Worth area]] and completed in 2009.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.dallasnews.com/news/frisco/2013/08/09/construction-of-7.5-million-karya-siddhi-hanuman-temple-to-serve-growing-hindu-community |title=Construction of $7.5 million Karya Siddhi Hanuman temple to serve growing Hindu community |first=Eden |last=Stiffman |work=Dallas News |date=August 9, 2013}}</ref> The main deity of the temple is [[Hanuman]]. The temple opened on July 23, 2009, and a week later, on August 1, it hosted the longest continuous chanting marathon with over 24 hours of recitation of [[Hanuman Chalisa]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/texas-temple-chant-guinness-record_us_55c92e9ae4b0f73b20ba7503 |title=Texas Hindu Temple Sets Guinness Record For Longest Chant |first= Antonia|last= Blumberg|date= August 11, 2015 |work=Huffington Post}}</ref> The temple is open all days of the week.
