{{italic title}}
The '''''Munich Manual of Demonic Magic''''' (CLM 849 of the [[Bavarian State Library]], [[Munich]]) is a fifteenth-century [[grimoire]] manuscript. The text, composed in Latin, is largely concerned with [[demonology]] and [[necromancy]].

[[Richard Kieckhefer]] edited the text of the manuscript in 1998 under the title ''Forbidden Rites: A Necromancer's Manual of the Fifteenth Century''. Portions of the text, in English translation, are presented in ''Forbidden Rites'' as well, embedded within the author's essays and explanations on the ''Munich Manual'' in specific and grimoires in general. The book has yet to be published in translation in its entirety.

