[[File:Ping Sien Si - 035 Shen Gongbao (15948173610).jpg|250px|thumbnail|right|Shen Gongbao a disciple of the Heavenly Primogenitor]] {{Chinese||s=申公豹 |t=申公豹 |p=Shēn Gōngbào }}
'''Shen Gongbao''' is a major character featured within the famed [[classic Chinese]] novel [[Investiture of the Gods]].<ref>{{cite book |author=[[Xu Zhonglin]] |script-title=zh:《封神演义》|date=2012-12-01 |publisher=Jiangxi Arts Publishing House |location=[[Nanchang]] |pages= |isbn=9787548018544 |language=zh}}</ref> Shen Gongbao is a disciple of [[Yuanshi Tianzun]], [[Jiang Ziya]]'s junior fellow apprentice.<ref>{{cite book |author=Xu Zhonglin |script-title=zh:《封神演义》|date=2010-01-01 |publisher=Changchun Publishing House |location=[[Changchun]] |pages= |isbn=9787544510806 |language=zh}}</ref>
==Background== Shen Gongbao is good at communication, and magic arts in general. When he left [[Kunlun Mountain]], he assisted [[King Zhou of Shang]] and regarded Jiang Ziya as his enemy.<ref>{{cite book |author=Xu Zhonglin |script-title=zh:《封神演义》|date=2013-05-01 |publisher=China Pictorial Publishing House |location=[[Beijing]] |pages= |isbn=9787514606966 |language=zh}}</ref>
Finally, Shen Gongbao was arrested by his master Yuanshi Tianzun.
Shen Gongbao was appointed as the General of East Sea ({{zh|t=|s=东海分水将军|hp=|links=no}}) in the end.<ref>{{cite book |author=Xu Zhonglin |script-title=zh:《封神演义》|date=2013-04-01 |publisher=Huaxia Publishing House |location=Beijing |pages= |isbn=9787508074986 |language=zh}}</ref>
