'''Tamaraikulam''' is a village in [[India]] near [[Kanyakumari (town)|Kanyakumari]]. On the advent of [[Ayyavazhi]] and the [[Swamithoppepathi]], the administrative unit was divided and part of it north to [[Swamithope]] is called [[North Tamaraikulam]]  and south as [[South Tamaraikulam]].

'''Thamaraiyur''' is the alternative name given for the village and the source for [[Ayyavazhi mythology]].


