{{Other uses|The Panda's Thumb (disambiguation)}}
{{Italic title}}
'''''The Panda's Thumb''''' is a [[blog]] on the [[creation–evolution controversy]] from a [[scientific consensus|mainstream scientific perspective]]. In 2006, ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]'' listed it as one of the top five science blogs,<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v442/n7098/full/442009a.html | title=Top five science blogs|publisher=''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]'' | year=2006 | first= | last= | accessdate = 2006-12-14}}</ref> and [[Mark Pallen]] has called it "the definitive blog on the evolution versus creationism debate".<ref>{{cite book|title=The Rough Guide to Evolution|first=Mark|last=Pallen|authorlink=Mark Pallen|series=[[Rough Guides]]|publisher=Penguin|year=2011|isbn=9781409358572|page=467|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oWe6BccoPtgC&pg=PT467}}</ref>

It is written by multiple contributors, including  [[Wesley R. Elsberry]], [[Paul R. Gross]], [[Nick Matzke]], [[PZ Myers]] and [[Mark Perakh]], many of whom also have complementary blogs at [[ScienceBlogs]]. The blog takes its name from The Panda's Thumb, the pub of the virtual [[University of Ediacara]], which is named after the [[The Panda's Thumb: More Reflections in Natural History|book of the same name]] by [[Stephen Jay Gould]], which in turn takes its title from the essay "The Panda's Peculiar Thumb",<ref>Gould, S. J. (1978). [http://www.stephenjaygould.org/library/gould_panda's-thumb.html "The panda's peculiar thumb."] ''Natural History'' 87 (Nov.): 20-30.</ref> which discusses the Panda's [[sesamoid bone]], an example of [[convergent evolution]].

